According to the country's information minister, the pair are under medical checks. KHARTOUM - Sudan suspects that two of its citizens who returned to the country from China are infected with the new coronavirus, the information minister told Reuters. One of the pair, a man and a woman, had been in the region of the Chinese city of Wuhan, the epicentre of the virus, Said Faisal Saleh. Both are under medical checks. WATCH: Coronavirus update: What we know so far 